content:
Define a Reporting Snapshot

After creating a source report and target object, you can define your reporting snapshot by naming it and choosing the source report that will load results into the target object. The running user determines the source report's level of access to data.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create, save, and schedule a reporting snapshot: Manage Reporting Snapshots
To run a reporting snapshot: Run Reports and Create on the target object

From Setup, enter “Reporting Snapshots” in the Quick Find box. Click New Reporting Snapshot.
Enter a name, unique name, and description for your reporting snapshot. Choose a user as the Running User.

Select a report from the Source Report drop-down list. Select a custom object from the Target Object drop-down list.

Map the fields on the source report to the fields on the target object using Save & Edit Field Mappings.
Click Save to save the definition of your reporting snapshot.
title: Defining a Reporting Snapshot in Salesforce
